Frequently Asked Questions for Vodafone Group PLC (NASDAQ:VOD)
What is Vodafone Group PLC's stock symbol?

Vodafone Group PLC trades on the NASDAQ under the ticker symbol "VOD."



How often does Vodafone Group PLC pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for Vodafone Group PLC?

Vodafone Group PLC declared a semiannual dividend on Thursday, May 18th. Shareholders of record on Friday, June 9th will be given a dividend of $1.1234 per share on Friday, August 4th. This represents a yield of 7.74%. The ex-dividend date is Wednesday, June 7th. This is a positive change from Vodafone Group PLC's previous semiannual dividend of $0.56.  View Vodafone Group PLC's Dividend History.



Where is Vodafone Group PLC's stock going? Where will Vodafone Group PLC's stock price be in 2017?

14 equities research analysts have issued 12 month price objectives for Vodafone Group PLC's shares. Their forecasts range from $30.00 to $32.00. On average, they anticipate Vodafone Group PLC's stock price to reach $31.00 in the next twelve months. View Analyst Ratings for Vodafone Group PLC.



Are investors shorting Vodafone Group PLC?

Vodafone Group PLC saw a drop in short interest in June. As of June 30th, there was short interest totalling 10,046,355 shares,  a drop of 33.2% from the June 15th total of 15,034,043 shares. Based on an average trading volume of 3,293,673 shares, the days-to-cover ratio is presently 3.1 days. 



Who are some of Vodafone Group PLC's key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to Vodafone Group PLC include AT&T (T), China Mobile (Hong Kong) (CHL), NTT DOCOMO (DCM), America Movil, S.A.B. de C.V. (AMX), America Movil SAB de CV (AMOV), China Telecom Corp Ltd (CHA), China Unicom (Hong Kong) Ltd (CHU), Sprint Corporation (S), Rogers Communication (RCI), SK Telecom Co. (SKM), Mobile TeleSystems OJSC (MBT), TIM Participacoes S.A. (TSU), BlackBerry Limited (BBRY), United States Cellular Corporation (USM), Telephone and Data Systems (TDS), Gogo (GOGO), Cellcom Israel (CEL) and ORBCOMM (ORBC).



Who are Vodafone Group PLC's key executives?

Vodafone Group PLC's management team includes the folowing people: Vittorio Colao, Chief Executive, Executive DirectorNicholas Jonathan Read, Chief Financial Officer, Executive DirectorHannes Ametsreiter, Chief Executive Officer – Vodafone GermanyVivek Badrinath, Chief Executive, Africa, Middle East and Asia-PacificAldo Bisio, Chief Executive Officer – Vodafone ItalyAntonio Coimbra, Chief Executive Officer – Vodafone SpainAhmed Essam, Chief Executive of Vodafone EgyptJeroen Hoencamp, Chief Executive of Vodafone NetherlandsNicholas Simon Jeffery, Chief Executive of Vodafone UKJohan Wibergh, Group Technology Officer



Who owns Vodafone Group PLC stock?

Vodafone Group PLC's stock is owned by a number of of institutional and retail investors. Top institutional shareholders include Fisher Asset Management LLC (0.00%), Hamlin Capital Management LLC (0.12%), Miller Howard Investments Inc. NY (0.10%), Janney Capital Management LLC (0.04%), Jarislowsky Fraser Ltd (0.00%) and Janney Montgomery Scott LLC (0.02%).  View Institutional Ownership Trends for Vodafone Group PLC.



Who sold Vodafone Group PLC stock? Who is selling Vodafone Group PLC stock?

Vodafone Group PLC's stock was sold by a variety of institutional investors in the last quarter, including Miller Howard Investments Inc. NY, Financial & Investment Management Group Ltd., Grandfield & Dodd LLC, CIBC Asset Management Inc, Wellington Shields Capital Management LLC, Stonebridge Capital Management Inc., ING Groep NV and BB&T Corp.  View Insider Buying and Selling for Vodafone Group PLC.



Who bought Vodafone Group PLC stock? Who is buying Vodafone Group PLC stock?

Vodafone Group PLC's stock was acquired by a variety of institutional investors in the last quarter, including Fisher Asset Management LLC, Howland Capital Management LLC, Janney Capital Management LLC, Lodestar Investment Counsel LLC IL, Cypress Asset Management Inc. TX, Aperio Group LLC, Bank of Montreal Can and Advisors Capital Management LLC.  View Insider Buying and Selling for Vodafone Group PLC.



How do I buy Vodafone Group PLC stock? 

Shares of Vodafone Group PLC can be purchased through any online brokerage account. Popular online brokerages include Vanguard Brokerage Services, TD Ameritrade, E*TRADE, Scottrade, Fidelity and Charles Schwab. 



What is Vodafone Group PLC's stock price today?

One share of Vodafone Group PLC stock can currently be purchased for approximately $29.44.


